[As mentioned previously, this website is constantly updated as new information comes in, so it is likely that when you read this post, the numbers will not match the linked numbers because they will have been updated since the post was prepared.

According to the data on the Johns Hopkins website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 119 132, with 80 954 cases reported by China. There are now a total of 38 034 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 114 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 5183 cases reported in the past 24 hours, with Italy accounting for 977 of the newly reported cases, Iran for 881 of newly reported cases, and South Korea for 277 of newly reported cases. There were 12 other countries with more than 50 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours were: Spain, 622; France, 575; Germany, 389; USA, 367; Norway, 195; Denmark, 172; Switzerland, 117; Sweden, 107; Japan, 70; Netherlands, 61; UK, 61; and Austria, 51. Of the 12 countries, 10 are in Europe. A global total of 4284 deaths have been reported, 1126 outside mainland China.

For the 13th consecutive day, more cases have been reported from outside mainland China than within mainland China. - Mod.MPP]

