[Note that the reporting interval is now midnight to midnight, presenting the full calendar day. In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 242 cases and 6 deaths. The epicenter of this outbreak is still Daegu province with 5794 reported cases and the surrounding province of Gyeongbuk with 1135 reported cases. Provinces reporting near or more than 100 cases include Gyeonggi (175). Seoul (193), Chungnam (112), and Busan (98).

While the number of newly confirmed cases today (10 Mar 2020) is 111 more cases than reported yesterday (9 Mar 2020) when 131 new cases were reported, the numbers are still significantly less than seen earlier. What bears watching is Seoul, where the daily increase In the past 24 hours was 52 cases, representing 21.5% of the daily increase in newly confirmed cases.

