[The tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Italy is now 10 149, including 631 deaths, up from 9172 cases and 463 deaths reported on 9 Mar 2020. Cases continue to be concentrated in Lombardy (5791), the epicenter of the outbreak, Emilia-Romagna (1533), and Venice (856), all in the northern part of the country. These 3 provinces account for 59.5% of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours.

72 hours ago, Italy announced a lockdown for the northern provinces where the outbreak was concentrated. 48 hours ago this was changed to be country wide. We shouldn't expect to see an impact until at least 1 incubation period has passed, as there are newly infected individuals who are still in their incubation period. The Public Health world is looking at Italy to see if this is feasible and if it has an impact in terms of slowing down transmission of the virus.

A dashboard similar to the Hopkins dashboard, including a map, produced by Italy showing the situation in real time, can be found at http://opendatadpc.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/b0c68bce2cce478eaac82fe38d4138b1.

A map of Italy showing regions can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/italy/regions.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7075036,75. - Mod.MPP]

